1
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:06,710
It's a relief.

2
00:01:08,490 --> 00:01:10,140
But I feel...

3
00:01:12,240 --> 00:01:14,770
It's so great, but...

4
00:01:14,770 --> 00:01:17,620
I guess I still can't believe it.

5
00:01:22,970 --> 00:01:24,880
It's scary.

6
00:01:26,710 --> 00:01:28,590
It's a relief,

7
00:01:28,590 --> 00:01:31,870
but it makes you worry, and you're scared, too.

8
00:01:31,870 --> 00:01:34,620
It's natural to feel that way.

9
00:01:37,360 --> 00:01:39,020
But look.

10
00:01:39,020 --> 00:01:43,120
Hyo Ri has such a dependable mom,

11
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:45,750
and there's Chef Kim, who's always on her side.

12
00:01:45,750 --> 00:01:48,800
And she has her friends.

13
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:51,110
She'll hang in there.

14
00:01:51,110 --> 00:01:52,670
Yes.

15
00:01:52,670 --> 00:01:54,240
Right.

16
00:01:56,200 --> 00:02:00,800
And you have me.

17
00:02:02,150 --> 00:02:06,140
I think it's your turn to lean on me, Ji An.

18
00:02:09,260 --> 00:02:12,050
I'll be by your side.

19
00:02:12,050 --> 00:02:15,860
Let's make sure to protect Hyo Ri.

20
00:02:15,860 --> 00:02:19,830
You just need to keep doing
what you've been doing.

21
00:02:19,830 --> 00:02:23,980
You've been doing a good job
without the need to do more.

22
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:41,360
So, I know it's hard to hear this,

23
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:46,080
but there are some things
you should know before the surgery.

24
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:49,960
You'll hear it with Hyo Ri
once you get to the hospital.

25
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:55,450
I thought it'd be better if you knew in advance.

26
00:02:59,990 --> 00:03:03,890
<i>In Hyo Ri's case, she'll be having awake surgery.</i>

27
00:03:03,890 --> 00:03:08,720
So, the surgery process might be harder for her.

28
00:03:08,720 --> 00:03:11,190
Nerve damage, seizures,

29
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:15,590
increased brain pressure, or cerebral edema.

30
00:03:15,590 --> 00:03:21,070
<i>Be aware that dangerous things
like those could occur.</i>

31
00:03:30,750 --> 00:03:32,420
<i>The location of the tumor</i>

32
00:03:32,420 --> 00:03:36,360
is near the part that's
in charge of language function.

33
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:38,520
After the surgery,

34
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:44,900
she might end up having language
disability as a side effect.

35
00:03:56,240 --> 00:04:00,600
[Episode 11. To you, who resembles me]

36
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,930
<i>When she's hospitalized next Tuesday</i>

37
00:04:04,930 --> 00:04:07,330
and gets surgery on Friday,

38
00:04:07,330 --> 00:04:09,920
I'll be away from the shop for two or three weeks.

39
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:12,050
It's a major surgery.

40
00:04:12,050 --> 00:04:13,650
Yes.

41
00:04:14,740 --> 00:04:19,360
But she'll recover quickly
since she's young, right?

42
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:23,410
- Yes.
- I should feed you guys health food before you go.

43
00:04:23,410 --> 00:04:25,660
I have tons of healthy ingredients.

44
00:04:25,660 --> 00:04:29,220
I'll feed Hyo Ri and you, too.

45
00:04:29,220 --> 00:04:31,100
Seon Yeong.

46
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:33,000
What?

47
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:36,710
You know Hyo Ri and I feel
so supported by you, right?

48
00:04:36,710 --> 00:04:38,790
Let's hang in there for her.

49
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:44,000
Of course. Hey, our menopause can be powerful.

50
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:45,950
We laugh and cry easily.

51
00:04:45,950 --> 00:04:48,290
Let's keep her confused next to her.

52
00:04:48,290 --> 00:04:51,390
We'll be sad, happy, sad, and happy.

53
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:55,200
Then, she'll be like, "I shouldn't be like them."
And get better quickly.

54
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,680
You're right.

55
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:59,460
Okay. Let's do that.

56
00:04:59,460 --> 00:05:01,780
Don't worry so much.

57
00:05:07,090 --> 00:05:11,070
I'll make you chicken soup.

58
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:19,610
Is he not here?

59
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:21,850
Huh? What's up?

60
00:05:21,850 --> 00:05:23,380
Are you here to see Bo Hyeon?

61
00:05:23,380 --> 00:05:24,870
I'm here to see you.

62
00:05:24,870 --> 00:05:26,710
Me?

63
00:05:26,710 --> 00:05:29,880
Would you like to go on a date
after you're off work?

64
00:05:34,550 --> 00:05:37,570
It's a bit early to eat, isn't it?

65
00:05:37,570 --> 00:05:40,390
It is. It's an awkward time.

66
00:05:44,790 --> 00:05:46,890
[Arcade]

67
00:05:46,890 --> 00:05:49,750
Should we hang out there and eat later?

68
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:51,110
Huh?

69
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:55,300
You really know how to play this?
This is a very old game.

70
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:58,700
While my friends studied English
and Math, I studied this game.

71
00:05:58,700 --> 00:06:00,540
Whenever my mom was stressed at work,

72
00:06:00,540 --> 00:06:03,220
she brought me to the arcade to play this.

73
00:06:03,220 --> 00:06:04,990
This is my forte.

74
00:06:04,990 --> 00:06:07,420
Don't be upset after you lose.

75
00:06:07,420 --> 00:06:08,780
You choose a character first.

76
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:12,000
Then, I'll choose Iori.

77
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:14,280
Iori.

78
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:16,020
Nice.

79
00:06:19,740 --> 00:06:22,020
Wow...

80
00:06:22,020 --> 00:06:23,990
<i>Ready, go.</i>

81
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:28,280
Geez. Hey!

82
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:34,700
And throw a punch at once and...

83
00:06:36,230 --> 00:06:37,860
<i>K.O.</i>

84
00:06:37,860 --> 00:06:39,510
Gosh.

85
00:06:39,510 --> 00:06:41,420
K.O.

86
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:45,380
Should we go?

87
00:06:45,380 --> 00:06:46,740
I can't leave like this.

88
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:48,200
Let's play another game.

89
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:50,880
I'll be Iori this time.

90
00:06:50,900 --> 00:06:54,700
The bad gamers always want
to switch characters after losing.

91
00:06:54,700 --> 00:06:56,450
You're just like your mom.

92
00:06:56,450 --> 00:06:58,540
You talk to yourself for others to hear.

93
00:06:58,540 --> 00:07:01,810
I learned that, too.

94
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:08,170
Let's go.

95
00:07:13,850 --> 00:07:16,840
The buttons aren't working. The buttons...

96
00:07:18,090 --> 00:07:19,680
Okay!

97
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:21,870
K.O.!

98
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:29,470
- Jump, jump, jump!
- Okay, okay!

99
00:07:31,590 --> 00:07:35,050
- I got it! I got it!
- Hold on! Hold on! Hold on!

100
00:07:35,050 --> 00:07:36,470
Okay!

101
00:07:36,470 --> 00:07:39,630
K.O.!

102
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:50,850
Go away.

103
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:53,400
You think this is fun? Go.

104
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:57,800
Should we stop?

105
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,680
I don't really feel like playing this.

106
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:01,630
Okay.

107
00:08:01,630 --> 00:08:03,380
Are you angry?

108
00:08:04,810 --> 00:08:09,270
Hyo Ri, I get very competitive
whenever I do something.

109
00:08:09,270 --> 00:08:11,850
I sometimes lose my cool.

110
00:08:11,850 --> 00:08:14,240
I guess you don't get frozen
shoulders and whatnot.

111
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:18,370
Your hands were as quick as most kids.

112
00:08:18,370 --> 00:08:20,550
Let's go eat since that was the plan.

113
00:08:20,550 --> 00:08:22,030
Okay, let's.

114
00:08:22,030 --> 00:08:25,990
What do you like? I'll get you anything you like.

115
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:30,000
I know it was a game, but I got so
beat up that I have no appetite.

116
00:08:33,460 --> 00:08:35,150
Should we go there?

117
00:08:35,150 --> 00:08:36,630
Huh?

118
00:08:36,630 --> 00:08:38,140
Let's eat something tasty.

119
00:08:38,140 --> 00:08:40,050
I said I'll treat you properly today.

120
00:08:40,050 --> 00:08:42,330
I've never been to a tented snack bar.

121
00:08:42,330 --> 00:08:44,620
I've always wanted to. Let's go.

122
00:08:44,620 --> 00:08:46,260
Let's go. Let's go.

123
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:58,530
Ahjussi, can I eat a lot?

124
00:08:58,530 --> 00:08:59,920
Listen to you.

125
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:02,310
Go ahead and fill up the table.

126
00:09:02,310 --> 00:09:04,890
If so, I'll...

127
00:09:04,890 --> 00:09:08,140
order pork rind and chicken gizzards.

128
00:09:08,140 --> 00:09:10,380
Yeah? Then, I'll...

129
00:09:10,380 --> 00:09:13,250
get chicken feet and spicy sea snails.

130
00:09:13,250 --> 00:09:16,000
Sounds good. Let's eat a lot and order more.

131
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:21,670
I have a generous heart,
but a generous stomach, too.

132
00:09:21,670 --> 00:09:23,500
Trust me.

133
00:09:25,890 --> 00:09:28,080
- Over here!
- Over here!

134
00:09:50,630 --> 00:09:54,130
Wow. You're a good eater.

135
00:09:54,130 --> 00:09:55,850
Good girl.

136
00:09:57,530 --> 00:09:59,430
What do you like the most?

137
00:10:02,010 --> 00:10:04,050
The pork rind.

138
00:10:04,050 --> 00:10:05,510
I've never had this before.

139
00:10:05,510 --> 00:10:07,420
It's totally my thing.

140
00:10:07,420 --> 00:10:09,600
I would've tried it sooner if I had known.

141
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:14,000
I know a really good pork rind spot nearby.

142
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:16,800
- Let's go there sometime.
- I'd love to.

143
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:23,500
But because of the surgery next week,
it's hard to plan it now.

144
00:10:23,550 --> 00:10:26,780
Anyway, promise to take me there sometime.

145
00:10:28,490 --> 00:10:32,160
I-Is the surgery happening sooner?

146
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:33,650
Well, yes.

147
00:10:33,650 --> 00:10:36,730
I got a call today that it'll happen next week.

148
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:59,500
Ahjussi, Mom is very clumsy around you, isn't she?

149
00:11:01,670 --> 00:11:03,420
I guess, a little?

150
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:07,350
It's because she's never been in a relationship.

151
00:11:07,350 --> 00:11:09,580
She adopted me when she was 23.

152
00:11:09,580 --> 00:11:13,850
She skipped over to be a mom even
before she had a chance to date.

153
00:11:15,490 --> 00:11:21,150
But thanks to you, she looks so happy these days.

154
00:11:22,300 --> 00:11:27,910
Being inexperienced can be good at our age.

155
00:11:27,910 --> 00:11:31,480
She's cute and very playful.

156
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:40,430
To summarize her life in a word,

157
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:44,310
it'd be "fighting."

158
00:11:44,310 --> 00:11:46,960
She might look dogged,

159
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:51,400
but she's straightforward, soft-hearted,

160
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:53,710
and she can't be calculative.

161
00:11:54,900 --> 00:12:00,900
She has just endured things
with child-like sincerity.

162
00:12:01,810 --> 00:12:04,280
<i>That means she's a good person.</i>

163
00:12:04,280 --> 00:12:07,770
So, when I think of Mom,

164
00:12:08,770 --> 00:12:11,050
it aches right here.

165
00:12:12,870 --> 00:12:15,010
<i>That means she feels for her.</i>

166
00:12:15,010 --> 00:12:19,980
But when I think of Mom, it also feels...

167
00:12:22,670 --> 00:12:24,540
like springtime in here.

168
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:29,900
I hope you feel that way, too.

169
00:12:30,890 --> 00:12:34,030
<i>She wants me to take good care of her mom.</i>

170
00:12:38,610 --> 00:12:42,930
I like her a lot.

171
00:12:45,930 --> 00:12:48,330
I won't make her feel lonely.

172
00:12:55,490 --> 00:12:57,950
Get me grilled eel.

173
00:13:01,390 --> 00:13:04,060
Okay. Let's.

174
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:07,200
Excuse me.

175
00:13:14,900 --> 00:13:16,840
Eat a lot.

176
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:18,950
This is good.

177
00:13:29,300 --> 00:13:31,380
So good.

178
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:52,910
- Ji An.
- Yes.

179
00:13:52,910 --> 00:13:54,300
Over there.

180
00:14:12,150 --> 00:14:13,740
Oppa.

181
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:16,570
Did you wait long?

182
00:14:16,570 --> 00:14:18,950
We finished a bit late today.

183
00:14:22,450 --> 00:14:24,650
I was just with Hyo Ri.

184
00:14:45,220 --> 00:14:47,320
I won't cry.

185
00:14:48,500 --> 00:14:52,680
You don't have to cry. But it's okay if you do.

186
00:14:52,680 --> 00:14:55,300
Say anything you want.

187
00:14:56,290 --> 00:14:58,870
And you don't have to say anything.

188
00:15:02,370 --> 00:15:06,410
Just do whatever you want to do.

189
00:15:09,220 --> 00:15:11,340
You can do that with me.

190
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:17,470
I swear I won't cry.

191
00:15:31,110 --> 00:15:33,340
You woke up when I was sleeping.

192
00:15:33,340 --> 00:15:37,510
I don't know why we're doing this so early.

193
00:15:37,510 --> 00:15:40,730
The doctor told you to work out.

194
00:15:40,730 --> 00:15:44,510
Walking barefoot like this
makes me feel energized.

195
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:48,150
Doesn't it already make you feel healthy?

196
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:52,830
You know how to influence people.

197
00:15:56,580 --> 00:15:58,350
Dr. Jung.

198
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:08,200
I feel so reassured having you
by Hyo Ri and Ji An's side.

199
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:13,140
So, I won't worry about Hyo Ri and feel anxious.

200
00:16:15,830 --> 00:16:19,630
I just hope it goes the way it should.

201
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:28,330
When does Tae Oh come back to work?

202
00:16:28,330 --> 00:16:32,160
I told him to enjoy his time with his mom fully.

203
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:34,480
Good job.

204
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:37,680
You're so generous, Chef Kim.

205
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:41,750
Did you just compliment me, Dr. Jung?

206
00:16:41,750 --> 00:16:44,770
Seeing that side of you when I had no expectation

207
00:16:44,770 --> 00:16:48,010
moves me a lot more.

208
00:16:50,170 --> 00:16:52,270
You aren't just generous.

209
00:16:52,270 --> 00:16:55,130
You're very thoughtful.

210
00:16:56,070 --> 00:16:58,170
I'm not that great.

211
00:16:59,590 --> 00:17:03,710
It'd be nice if you were
a little better at reading the air.

212
00:17:03,710 --> 00:17:07,870
When I was in school, kids said
I had an eye on the back of my head.

213
00:17:07,900 --> 00:17:11,600
Because I was so quick, they said
I had an eye on the back of my head.

214
00:17:11,610 --> 00:17:14,710
That's what they used to say. You know?

215
00:17:16,850 --> 00:17:18,210
Really?

216
00:17:18,210 --> 00:17:20,310
Let's just say it's true.

217
00:17:25,810 --> 00:17:27,770
She offends subtly.

218
00:17:27,770 --> 00:17:29,940
It's strangely offensive.

219
00:17:29,940 --> 00:17:32,230
But I lose if I get offended now.

220
00:17:32,230 --> 00:17:33,620
I'm not offended.

221
00:17:33,620 --> 00:17:36,030
I don't get affected so easily.

222
00:17:41,420 --> 00:17:44,270
- You came.
<i>- Hey.</i>

223
00:17:52,100 --> 00:17:55,180
Let's lend our hands at Hyo Ri's shop.

224
00:17:55,180 --> 00:17:57,120
We can each pick a day.

225
00:17:57,120 --> 00:18:00,130
And don't ask Hyo Ri detailed
questions about the surgery.

226
00:18:00,130 --> 00:18:02,900
I'll do research. Ask me instead.

227
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:05,540
She must be anxious already.

228
00:18:05,540 --> 00:18:09,260
How about you? Won't you do anything?

229
00:18:10,260 --> 00:18:12,960
I'll take care of her mental state.

230
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:17,400
I'll tell her not to cry and get her act together.

231
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:21,350
Did you do military training secretly?
She's like a military senior.

232
00:18:21,350 --> 00:18:24,150
Leave her alone, you bastard.

233
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:26,910
- What did I do?
- Shit.

234
00:18:27,850 --> 00:18:29,960
It breaks my heart.

235
00:18:31,810 --> 00:18:36,100
She's tough, but she's delicate.

236
00:18:36,860 --> 00:18:40,730
She may sound tough, but she gets easily scared.

237
00:18:40,730 --> 00:18:43,460
She's fragile. What do we do?

238
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:47,340
She probably can't show her struggles.

239
00:18:49,010 --> 00:18:53,190
That makes me even sadder.

240
00:18:54,120 --> 00:18:55,570
It's okay.

241
00:18:58,790 --> 00:19:00,780
She'll be okay.

242
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:04,500
So, cry all you want here,
and don't cry in front of her.

243
00:19:10,020 --> 00:19:14,000
Why does he look so skinny already?

244
00:19:20,790 --> 00:19:22,760
[Operation prep / Order of operation]

245
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:24,240
[Post-op]

246
00:19:24,240 --> 00:19:25,830
<i>Bo Hyeon.</i>

247
00:19:35,410 --> 00:19:38,850
I'll be driving Hyo Ri to the hospital tomorrow.

248
00:19:38,850 --> 00:19:40,900
Have you seen her?

249
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:43,270
We'll meet briefly later.

250
00:19:44,590 --> 00:19:46,400
How do you feel?

251
00:19:48,190 --> 00:19:50,560
Complicated.

252
00:19:51,530 --> 00:19:54,530
I'm thinking about what I can do.

253
00:19:58,220 --> 00:20:01,100
You share the same worry as I do.

254
00:20:02,510 --> 00:20:05,490
I've heard sincerity is powerful.

255
00:20:05,490 --> 00:20:08,280
Let's ask ourselves how we really feel.

256
00:20:10,370 --> 00:20:13,050
When will it stop raining?

257
00:20:14,250 --> 00:20:16,180
It'll stop soon.

258
00:20:20,730 --> 00:20:23,960
<i>We aren't open yet.</i>

259
00:20:23,960 --> 00:20:26,280
Huh? Tae Oh.

260
00:20:26,280 --> 00:20:27,330
I know.

261
00:20:27,330 --> 00:20:31,010
You missed me a lot since I've been gone, right?

262
00:20:31,010 --> 00:20:32,470
You're right.

263
00:20:32,470 --> 00:20:34,280
- Have you been well?
- Yes.

264
00:20:34,280 --> 00:20:36,710
Gosh, the crown daisy will flower soon.

265
00:20:36,710 --> 00:20:38,860
Seon Yeong.

266
00:20:38,860 --> 00:20:41,660
Gosh. Why are you back so early, Tae Oh?

267
00:20:41,660 --> 00:20:43,920
