00:39:28,430 --> 00:39:30,440
<i>Really?</i>

538
00:39:30,440 --> 00:39:33,800
How about you? Did you eat?

539
00:39:33,800 --> 00:39:35,500
Seon Yeong.

540
00:39:35,500 --> 00:39:36,560
<i>Yes.</i>

541
00:39:36,560 --> 00:39:38,820
Did you know?

542
00:39:38,820 --> 00:39:42,550
Love is visible.

543
00:39:59,190 --> 00:40:01,620
<i>Right. Here.</i>

544
00:40:14,110 --> 00:40:15,790
<i>Eat.</i>

545
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:21,930
Love was something you could see.

546
00:40:21,930 --> 00:40:23,840
<i>What are you saying?</i>

547
00:40:23,840 --> 00:40:28,400
Hey, I saw the devil
while you were seeing love today.

548
00:40:28,400 --> 00:40:31,160
<i>What will you do about the Village Leader?</i>

549
00:40:31,160 --> 00:40:33,910
<i>She would've been a slave hunter
if she were born in the Joseon era.</i>

550
00:40:33,910 --> 00:40:36,670
<i>Jang Hyuk* is nothing compared to her.</i>
(Actor, referring to his drama)

551
00:40:36,670 --> 00:40:38,550
<i>What do I do?</i>

552
00:40:38,550 --> 00:40:40,150
<i>What do I do, Ji An?</i>

553
00:40:40,150 --> 00:40:43,340
<i>I'm so lonely and exhausted. I'm hungry, too.</i>

554
00:40:43,340 --> 00:40:45,800
Aigoo, aigoo. I'm sorry.

555
00:40:45,800 --> 00:40:49,610
[Seoul Yushim Hospital]

556
00:40:49,610 --> 00:40:51,350
The test results looked good.

557
00:40:51,350 --> 00:40:54,030
We'll proceed with the surgery as planned.

558
00:40:54,030 --> 00:40:57,520
The tumor is in the frontal lobe,
which is called Broca's area.

559
00:40:57,520 --> 00:41:00,000
It's in charge of language function.

560
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:03,170
The size is about 3 cm.

561
00:41:03,170 --> 00:41:06,560
As I said, it will be an awake operation.

562
00:41:06,560 --> 00:41:09,970
The duration will be about six hours.

563
00:41:09,970 --> 00:41:13,350
Can you remove the entire tumor?

564
00:41:13,350 --> 00:41:15,920
We need to have a look...

565
00:41:15,920 --> 00:41:18,030
We need to have a look at it first to find out.

566
00:41:18,030 --> 00:41:20,500
Since it's near the language function area,

567
00:41:20,500 --> 00:41:23,040
we're doing an awake operation.

568
00:41:23,040 --> 00:41:26,160
But we won't remove it forcibly.

569
00:41:26,160 --> 00:41:28,970
If we can't remove the entire tumor,

570
00:41:28,970 --> 00:41:32,580
we'll treat it in another way while monitoring it.

571
00:41:32,580 --> 00:41:34,580
Don't worry.

572
00:41:36,800 --> 00:41:38,670
We'll do a mock test before the surgery to

573
00:41:38,700 --> 00:41:42,100
get familiar with the flow
of the procedure. Don't worry.

574
00:41:42,100 --> 00:41:44,600
I heard you were in medical school.

575
00:41:44,600 --> 00:41:45,670
Yes.

576
00:41:45,670 --> 00:41:47,430
You must know how I feel, then.

577
00:41:47,430 --> 00:41:49,850
I'll make sure to do my best.

578
00:41:49,900 --> 00:41:54,200
Let's trust each other and calmly work together.

579
00:41:54,210 --> 00:41:55,520
Okay.

580
00:41:56,300 --> 00:41:58,760
There are some complications

581
00:41:58,760 --> 00:42:02,080
you should be aware of after the operation.

582
00:42:02,080 --> 00:42:04,690
During the operation, there could be complications

583
00:42:04,690 --> 00:42:08,720
such as bleeding, seizure, and cerebral edema.

584
00:42:08,720 --> 00:42:11,240
After the operation,

585
00:42:12,200 --> 00:42:15,500
there could be a language
disability, mental deterioration...

586
00:42:32,210 --> 00:42:34,000
Hello.

587
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:35,660
Hey, Sook.

588
00:42:35,660 --> 00:42:37,210
Hello.

589
00:42:43,330 --> 00:42:45,020
Hello, Dr. Jung.

590
00:42:45,020 --> 00:42:46,680
Long time no see.

591
00:42:46,680 --> 00:42:50,730
I'll make sure to cheer Hyo Ri up.

592
00:42:54,610 --> 00:42:56,880
I'll hurry back.

593
00:42:56,880 --> 00:43:00,140
Take your time. There isn't much going on today.

594
00:43:06,430 --> 00:43:07,990
Sook.

595
00:43:10,200 --> 00:43:12,490
Hey, why do you look so good in the gown?

596
00:43:12,490 --> 00:43:16,770
I know. Why do I make everything look hip?

597
00:43:16,770 --> 00:43:19,700
Do you have another one?
I think I would look good, too.

598
00:43:19,700 --> 00:43:21,120
What's that?

599
00:43:22,150 --> 00:43:24,100
When you have too much on your mind,

600
00:43:24,100 --> 00:43:25,890
Sakuragi Hanamichi is the best.

601
00:43:27,650 --> 00:43:30,300
This would be perfect for the next three days.

602
00:43:30,300 --> 00:43:33,140
Time to meet Rukawa again.

603
00:43:33,140 --> 00:43:36,410
It's a problem that the kids
these days don't read books.

604
00:43:36,410 --> 00:43:39,850
Comic books or webtoons are nice,

605
00:43:39,850 --> 00:43:44,470
but read something serious to improve
reading comprehension skills.

606
00:43:46,930 --> 00:43:50,080
I was just talking to myself. Don't mind me.

607
00:43:51,260 --> 00:43:52,630
Okay.

608
00:44:08,710 --> 00:44:10,310
Shall we?

609
00:44:28,780 --> 00:44:33,330
<i>She was a friend who brought me comfort back then.</i>

610
00:44:37,300 --> 00:44:39,130
Cho Rong,

611
00:44:39,130 --> 00:44:43,960
my mom... My mom left me.

612
00:44:48,910 --> 00:44:50,770
It's okay.

613
00:44:50,770 --> 00:44:52,630
Again?

614
00:44:53,210 --> 00:44:55,320
Your father did it again?

615
00:44:55,320 --> 00:44:57,450
It's okay.

616
00:44:59,530 --> 00:45:03,550
I have you. So, it's okay.

617
00:45:03,550 --> 00:45:08,240
<i>We just felt bad for each other.</i>

618
00:45:08,940 --> 00:45:11,050
<i>We planned to start a hair salon in Seoul.</i>

619
00:45:11,050 --> 00:45:13,640
<i>So, we attended a beauty school.</i>

620
00:45:13,640 --> 00:45:18,810
<i>But she unexpectedly got pregnant with Hyo Ri.</i>

621
00:45:18,810 --> 00:45:21,450
<i>The baby's father was a hopeless kid.</i>

622
00:45:21,450 --> 00:45:25,080
<i>It was obvious what would happen
if her family found out.</i>

623
00:45:25,080 --> 00:45:28,170
<i>So, we ran away to Seoul and had Hyo Ri.</i>

624
00:45:29,940 --> 00:45:33,370
<i>Lee Hyo Ri was the biggest star then.</i>

625
00:45:33,370 --> 00:45:35,900
<i>I wanted our baby to be as cool as her.</i>

626
00:45:35,900 --> 00:45:38,320
<i>That's why we named her Hyo Ri.</i>

627
00:45:38,320 --> 00:45:40,750
<i>That's how childish we were.</i>

628
00:45:50,250 --> 00:45:52,500
[Han Cho Rong]

629
00:46:02,040 --> 00:46:04,720
You're making me feel bad.

630
00:46:04,720 --> 00:46:07,260
Why are you smiling so beautifully?

631
00:46:08,710 --> 00:46:11,170
It's been too long, hasn't it?

632
00:46:12,780 --> 00:46:18,720
I just couldn't muster up the courage to see you.

633
00:46:22,160 --> 00:46:24,490
Handkerchief. Hand me the handkerchief.

634
00:46:25,610 --> 00:46:26,910
Hey.

635
00:46:26,910 --> 00:46:28,350
Huh?

636
00:46:28,350 --> 00:46:29,650
Okay.

637
00:46:30,660 --> 00:46:32,040
Here.

638
00:46:46,750 --> 00:46:52,090
I'll raise Hyo Ri like a princess.

639
00:46:54,590 --> 00:46:59,080
Yes. Let's not raise her like
our parents raised us.

640
00:47:00,830 --> 00:47:02,570
Ji An,

641
00:47:03,510 --> 00:47:05,510
I won't...

642
00:47:07,900 --> 00:47:13,400
even think about raising her differently
than my parents did or things like that.

643
00:47:13,500 --> 00:47:20,600
I'll make sure my Hyo Ri never
finds out how I was raised.

644
00:47:20,610 --> 00:47:23,820
I'll only give her good things.

645
00:47:26,420 --> 00:47:29,290
I'll only make her happy.

646
00:47:31,880 --> 00:47:34,360
I'm serious.

647
00:47:45,120 --> 00:47:46,760
Let's do that.

648
00:47:46,760 --> 00:47:48,740
For sure.

649
00:47:48,740 --> 00:47:50,560
Let's make sure to do that.

650
00:47:57,460 --> 00:47:59,210
Cho Rong,

651
00:48:00,930 --> 00:48:03,670
I don't think I was able to.

652
00:48:05,310 --> 00:48:07,810
I wanted to...

653
00:48:09,090 --> 00:48:13,240
but I don't think I raised her that way.

654
00:48:14,050 --> 00:48:16,540
I didn't want to.

655
00:48:17,520 --> 00:48:20,390
But since I'm not a good mom,

656
00:48:21,170 --> 00:48:24,020
I knew nothing.

657
00:48:25,300 --> 00:48:28,880
Hyo Ri was sick, but I had no idea.

658
00:48:29,610 --> 00:48:34,280
I was too ashamed to come and visit you.

659
00:48:35,430 --> 00:48:36,970
Sorry.

660
00:48:39,010 --> 00:48:41,950
I'm sorry, Cho Rong.

661
00:48:42,950 --> 00:48:46,000
But please protect Hyo Ri.

662
00:48:47,420 --> 00:48:50,350
I keep thinking about it,

663
00:48:50,350 --> 00:48:54,230
but you're the only person I could ask.

664
00:48:54,230 --> 00:48:56,850
Cho Rong, please protect...

665
00:48:56,850 --> 00:48:59,910
Please protect our Hyo Ri. Please...

666
00:49:05,210 --> 00:49:09,110
Please protect our Hyo Ri...

667
00:49:34,620 --> 00:49:37,790
All right. Here they are. Enjoy.

668
00:49:37,790 --> 00:49:40,070
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

669
00:49:40,070 --> 00:49:42,170
One bossam and two lunch sets.

670
00:49:42,170 --> 00:49:44,460
I told them that our bossam is amazing.

671
00:49:44,460 --> 00:49:46,250
You're the best. Welcome.

672
00:49:46,250 --> 00:49:48,950
- Welcome.
- Have a seat over there.

673
00:49:49,730 --> 00:49:53,270
Two lunch sets and bossam.

674
00:49:58,460 --> 00:49:59,740
Chef.

675
00:50:00,500 --> 00:50:03,900
Yes. Yes, I heard. Sorry.

676
00:50:05,220 --> 00:50:06,860
Are you okay?

677
00:50:07,890 --> 00:50:10,890
Yes. Ever since Village Leader Go came,

678
00:50:10,890 --> 00:50:13,630
we're getting so many customers. It's hard.

679
00:50:15,020 --> 00:50:18,080
Hyo Ri will be okay.

680
00:50:19,470 --> 00:50:20,970
Yes.

681
00:50:31,270 --> 00:50:34,760
Saying, "You must be tired," would be normal.

682
00:50:34,760 --> 00:50:38,680
But I want to ask, "Do you even feel tired?"

683
00:50:40,460 --> 00:50:44,260
Back in my day, I ran a baekban* place briefly.
(Home-made style meal)

684
00:50:44,260 --> 00:50:47,430
My gosh, because I was reminded of those days,

685
00:50:47,430 --> 00:50:50,240
my old spirit kicked in.

686
00:50:50,240 --> 00:50:52,960
No wonder.

687
00:50:54,490 --> 00:50:59,260
Anyway, I'm tired. But I feel so secure
because you're here.

688
00:50:59,260 --> 00:51:01,350
- Really?
- Yes.

689
00:51:09,000 --> 00:51:13,300
Your body is here, but your heart is in Seoul.

690
00:51:17,480 --> 00:51:21,970
Our Hyo Ri is incredibly strong.

691
00:51:21,970 --> 00:51:26,690
And she even went to medical school.

692
00:51:28,950 --> 00:51:35,360
I'm sure she knows a lot more than we do.

693
00:51:35,360 --> 00:51:38,330
Why should I worry?

694
00:51:38,330 --> 00:51:42,300
I should be trusting and supporting
her now, and that wouldn't be enough.

695
00:51:45,220 --> 00:51:47,540
You know how people tell me,

696
00:51:47,540 --> 00:51:50,900
"Ms. Go, you're so strong."

697
00:51:50,900 --> 00:51:53,690
That I look so easygoing and magnanimous.

698
00:51:53,690 --> 00:51:55,760
People say that often to me.

699
00:51:55,760 --> 00:51:58,180
But in here.

700
00:51:58,200 --> 00:52:03,400
Right in here. A fragile girl is living here.

701
00:52:05,020 --> 00:52:08,290
I could tell you're...

702
00:52:08,290 --> 00:52:10,180
similar to me.

703
00:52:10,180 --> 00:52:14,010
You don't easily say you're struggling, right?

704
00:52:17,960 --> 00:52:19,860
But Chef Kim,

705
00:52:20,620 --> 00:52:22,580
don't live like that.

706
00:52:23,280 --> 00:52:25,030
Pardon?

707
00:52:25,030 --> 00:52:27,320
Stop crying inside.

708
00:52:29,120 --> 00:52:31,770
Just cry openly.

709
00:52:31,770 --> 00:52:36,730
That way, someone would
hold your hand and hug you.

710
00:52:36,730 --> 00:52:39,620
It might not be much,

711
00:52:39,620 --> 00:52:44,470
but you can hear some words of comfort, you know?

712
00:52:44,470 --> 00:52:46,610
Isn't that what affection is?

713
00:52:46,610 --> 00:52:52,180
Isn't that why we're all living together
like this and nagging each other?

714
00:52:52,230 --> 00:52:53,740
Right?

715
00:53:21,660 --> 00:53:23,090
Give me Volume 5.

716
00:53:23,090 --> 00:53:25,520
Wow, you read so fast.

717
00:53:25,520 --> 00:53:27,080
I'm a doctor.

718
00:53:29,660 --> 00:53:32,820
Doctors sure are different.

719
00:53:33,790 --> 00:53:36,470
Wow. Rukawa is so cool.

720
00:53:36,470 --> 00:53:38,310
How come no one like him exists in real life?

721
00:53:38,310 --> 00:53:39,930
There's Bo Hyeon.

722
00:53:44,180 --> 00:53:47,320
Hey, you got funnier.

723
00:53:47,320 --> 00:53:51,480
Hush. How dare you compare him to Rukawa?

724
00:53:51,480 --> 00:53:55,890
To be honest, Bo Hyeon has
a face you easily get sick of.

725
00:53:55,890 --> 00:53:58,200
His face is too tiny.

726
00:53:58,200 --> 00:54:02,200
He doesn't feel like a real man, you know.

727
00:54:02,240 --> 00:54:04,540
Lucky you for having a big manly face.

728
00:54:04,540 --> 00:54:07,780
My face isn't big. It's medium-sized.

729
00:54:13,660 --> 00:54:15,150
Hi.

730
00:54:17,900 --> 00:54:21,760
Lee Sook, isn't this your teacher?

731
00:54:21,760 --> 00:54:24,630
I bet no one messed around with you.

732
00:54:24,630 --> 00:54:28,730
When I was in 10th grade,
a teacher-in-training used to bow to me.

733
00:54:28,730 --> 00:54:32,250
Right. He did that for a whole semester.

734
00:54:32,250 --> 00:54:33,760
I got caught by the dean,

735
00:54:33,760 --> 00:54:35,890
so I ran on the track until I threw up.

736
00:54:35,890 --> 00:54:37,810
But it was fun.

737
00:54:37,810 --> 00:54:41,750
By the way, when was Hyo Ri ever not pretty?

738
00:54:41,800 --> 00:54:45,100
I'm sure I could find some pictures.
But I really don't remember.

739
00:54:45,100 --> 00:54:46,340
I don't see any.

740
00:54:46,340 --> 00:54:49,320
Geez. Give me a break.

741
00:54:49,320 --> 00:54:50,970
This is why I don't date.

742
00:54:50,970 --> 00:54:53,230
It ruins you.

743
00:54:53,230 --> 00:54:55,080
Geez, seriously.

744
00:54:55,080 --> 00:54:57,380
I'm going to work. Bye.

745
00:54:57,380 --> 00:54:58,420
I'll be back tomorrow.

746
00:54:58,420 --> 00:54:59,870
I said don't come.

747
00:54:59,870 --> 00:55:03,170
When someone tells me to come, I don't want to go.

748
00:55:03,170 --> 00:55:05,080
When someone tells me not to, I want to go.

749
00:55:05,080 --> 00:55:06,620
Hey.

750
00:55:06,620 --> 00:55:08,300
Dr. Jung.

751
00:55:08,940 --> 00:55:10,980
Buy me something tasty.

752
00:55:12,260 --> 00:55:14,740
Me? Why?

753
00:55:15,960 --> 00:55:18,840
I'm so lonely because they're so lovey-dovey.

754
00:55:18,840 --> 00:55:20,340
I'm really sad.

755
00:55:20,340 --> 00:55:22,160
And you're a doctor.

756
00:55:22,160 --> 00:55:24,060
It's the doctor's treat.

757
00:55:24,700 --> 00:55:27,310
I want something expensive and sweet.

758
00:55:27,310 --> 00:55:29,290
Or something expensive and filling.

759
00:55:29,290 --> 00:55:32,830
I'll bring you more Slam Dunk volumes.
Let's go. Let's go.

760
00:55:44,250 --> 00:55:46,170
What did you do to me that

761
00:55:46,170 --> 00:55:48,970
I missed you so much when
I didn't see you for only a day?

762
00:55:48,970 --> 00:55:51,150
Did you miss me a lot?

763
00:55:51,150 --> 00:55:52,540
Yes.

764
00:55:55,750 --> 00:55:57,630
I'll come before you go in
for the surgery tomorrow.

765
00:55:57,630 --> 00:56:01,240
And I'll be by your side when you wake up.

766
00:56:11,700 --> 00:56:17,200
Do you know the hardest thing when you're sick?

767
00:56:18,690 --> 00:56:22,740
That my everyday life and the lives
of those people around me pause.

768
00:56:22,740 --> 00:56:25,300
They even disappear.

769
00:56:26,300 --> 00:56:31,200
My surgery will go well, and I'll come
back after my treatment.

770
00:56:31,240 --> 00:56:32,960
So, don't come.

771
00:56:34,100 --> 00:56:37,990
While you keep living your everyday life,

772
00:56:38,000 --> 00:56:44,200
I'll find my new everyday life and come back.

773
00:56:44,220 --> 00:56:46,930
That would be an even bigger encouragement for me.

774
00:56:49,390 --> 00:56:51,710
Is that what you want?

775
00:56:55,850 --> 00:56:58,920
When you got sick when we were on our trip,

776
00:57:01,130 --> 00:57:04,490
I was so upset to see you in pain.

777
00:57:05,470 --> 00:57:07,590
That's when I thought...

778
00:57:09,180 --> 00:57:11,570
you must've felt...

779
00:57:13,100 --> 00:57:19,300
a lot more pain than I do while seeing me sick.

780
00:57:22,260 --> 00:57:23,800
Thank you.

781
00:57:24,770 --> 00:57:27,510
You must be upset and heartbroken.

782
00:57:27,510 --> 00:57:30,620
But you're making me feel secure
without showing it.

783
00:57:34,710 --> 00:57:37,050
I'm your boyfriend.

784
00:57:37,050 --> 00:57:39,010
I love you the most in this world.

785
00:57:39,010 --> 00:57:41,310
There's nothing I can't do for you.

786
00:57:46,940 --> 00:57:50,420
Here. You must be tired from acting strong.

787
00:57:50,420 --> 00:57:52,850
Lean on me and rest.

788
00:58:24,430 --> 00:58:26,530
[Seoul Yushim Hospital]

789
00:58:26,530 --> 00:58:29,490
We'll enter the OR following the schedule.

790
00:58:29,490 --> 00:58:32,780
She'll be sent to the ICU right afterward.

791
00:58:32,780 --> 00:58:35,710
If we don't detect any complications,
we'll move her

792
00:58:35,710 --> 00:58:38,000
to the regular ward after a couple of days.

793
00:58:38,000 --> 00:58:42,390
You'll see what I just told you right here.

794
00:58:42,390 --> 00:58:45,350
Please read through it and sign.

795
00:58:45,350 --> 00:58:46,850
Okay, got it.

796
00:58:46,850 --> 00:58:50,600
And we need to cut your scalp in some places.

797
00:58:50,600 --> 00:58:56,900
I suggest getting ready before going
to the OR to shorten the operation time.

798
00:58:56,940 --> 00:58:58,390
Okay, got it.

799
00:58:58,390 --> 00:59:00,480
Please take your time reading it.

800
00:59:00,480 --> 00:59:04,940
I'll be outside. Ask me if you have any questions.

801
00:59:04,940 --> 00:59:07,930
Ma'am, I'd like to discuss something
about the room with you.

802
00:59:07,930 --> 00:59:09,410
Please see me for a moment.

803
00:59:09,410 --> 00:59:10,750
Okay.

804
00:59:24,310 --> 00:59:26,930
[Operation goal]

805
00:59:30,000 --> 00:59:33,620
[Surgeon in charge]

806
01:00:27,830 --> 01:00:32,930
[Seoul Yushim Hospital]

807
01:00:40,080 --> 01:00:41,780
You're up.

808
01:00:42,830 --> 01:00:44,470
You couldn't sleep.

809
01:00:44,470 --> 01:00:46,430
No, I did.

810
01:00:46,430 --> 01:00:50,660
Dr. Jung went to see Dr. Lee briefly.

811
01:00:52,040 --> 01:00:53,970
Mom,

812
01:00:53,970 --> 01:00:57,550
in my dream, I was upset that someone
kept saying I didn't look like you.

813
01:00:57,550 --> 01:01:00,330
Really? Who said that?

814
01:01:01,850 --> 01:01:03,590
I look like you, right?

815
01:01:03,590 --> 01:01:04,760
Of course.

816
01:01:04,760 --> 01:01:06,870
You look just like when I was 23.

817
01:01:06,870 --> 01:01:08,520
Right?

818
01:01:11,060 --> 01:01:14,270
It'll take some time until I wake up
after the surgery.

819
01:01:14,270 --> 01:01:18,660
- Don't be upset and impatient.
- Okay.

820
01:01:18,660 --> 01:01:23,130
And once I stabilize, let's go on a trip together.

821
01:01:23,130 --> 01:01:25,890
Yes. That's a good idea.

822
01:01:25,890 --> 01:01:27,790
Let's make sure to go.

823
01:01:28,690 --> 01:01:31,380
I have another reason to fight.

824
01:01:38,810 --> 01:01:40,820
Is the patient feeling okay?

825
01:01:40,820 --> 01:01:42,590
I think she's okay now.

826
01:01:42,590 --> 01:01:45,110
I'll come by to check the blood pressure later.

827
01:01:45,110 --> 01:01:46,870
Okay. Thank you.

828
01:01:48,600 --> 01:01:49,600
How come you're together?

829
01:01:49,640 --> 01:01:51,400
We ran into each other at the front.

830
01:01:51,400 --> 01:01:54,000
Say hi to Hyo Ri. She'll go up at nine.

831
01:01:54,030 --> 01:01:55,400
Okay.

832
01:02:09,030 --> 01:02:13,640
Hey, Lee Hyo Ri. I came with Mr. Ryu. He said-

833
01:02:15,800 --> 01:02:17,740
What's the deal?

834
01:02:17,740 --> 01:02:21,160
Can't you manage your facial expression?
Are you shocked?

835
01:02:25,190 --> 01:02:27,280
Sook.

836
01:02:38,600 --> 01:02:42,530
My dad said he'd kill me if I cried.

837
01:02:43,480 --> 01:02:45,780
Hey, don't cry.

838
01:02:45,780 --> 01:02:48,960
In a movie I saw, a friend shaved
her hair along with her friend.

839
01:02:48,960 --> 01:02:51,400
Do you want to shave yours if you're so sad?

840
01:02:51,400 --> 01:02:52,820
No.

841
01:02:54,530 --> 01:02:58,570
Gosh, why do you look like that?

842
01:03:10,630 --> 01:03:14,880
It's nice that I can't cry because
you're sobbing, my friend.

843
01:03:16,740 --> 01:03:19,120
Stop crying.

844
01:03:19,120 --> 01:03:21,850
I'm okay. Come on.

845
01:03:24,340 --> 01:03:26,730
You're okay, right?

846
01:04:04,280 --> 01:04:07,650
<i>People who resemble each other when they're sad.</i>

847
01:04:07,650 --> 01:04:10,290
Will your hair grow back quickly?

848
01:04:11,990 --> 01:04:14,460
You must look so ugly.

849
01:04:14,460 --> 01:04:19,230
<i>We try to hide our broken hearts by smiling</i>

850
01:04:19,230 --> 01:04:22,400
<i>and acting calm not to appear sad.</i>

851
01:04:36,680 --> 01:04:39,980
<i>But our sadness ends up getting found out.</i>

852
01:04:40,980 --> 01:04:44,480
<i>That's how we resemble each other.</i>

853
01:04:52,670 --> 01:04:57,180
<i>That's why I pretend I didn't notice your sadness.</i>

854
01:04:58,970 --> 01:05:01,510
<i>Because I can imagine</i>

855
01:05:01,510 --> 01:05:08,380
<i>how desperately you want to push that
sadness away as much as you love me.</i>

856
01:05:08,380 --> 01:05:10,910
[Operation Room]

857
01:05:10,910 --> 01:05:15,420
<i>Because I want to protect
your effort until the end.</i>

858
01:05:17,970 --> 01:05:19,560
Mom,

859
01:05:20,890 --> 01:05:22,610
let's go with a fighting spirit.

860
01:05:23,610 --> 01:05:25,550
Let's go fighting.

861
01:05:27,470 --> 01:05:29,830
The patient will go in.

862
01:05:57,070 --> 01:06:02,570
<i>Just as you, who resemble me,
protected me from my sadness.</i>

863
01:06:08,140 --> 01:06:09,740
Bo Hyeon.

864
01:06:09,740 --> 01:06:10,890
Yes.

865
01:06:10,890 --> 01:06:12,870
Let me ask you a favor.

866
01:06:16,440 --> 01:06:18,550
- Do I look okay?
- You think?

867
01:06:18,550 --> 01:06:20,870
You look amazing.

868
01:06:22,960 --> 01:06:24,940
Should I start?

869
01:06:24,940 --> 01:06:26,330
Yes.

870
01:06:33,460 --> 01:06:35,120
Mom...

871
01:06:48,740 --> 01:06:52,980
When I first learned I was sick,

872
01:06:55,570 --> 01:06:59,100
I thought it was a bit unfair.

873
01:07:01,790 --> 01:07:04,980
Everyone takes their family,

874
01:07:04,980 --> 01:07:08,230
their lives in their 30s and 40s,

875
01:07:10,600 --> 01:07:13,540
and tomorrow for granted.

876
01:07:13,540 --> 01:07:16,770
Why is nothing guaranteed for me?

877
01:07:21,030 --> 01:07:23,370
But thinking now,

878
01:07:26,400 --> 01:07:30,420
one thing is guaranteed in my life.

879
01:07:35,300 --> 01:07:37,250
It's that you're...

880
01:07:39,900 --> 01:07:44,100
That you're my mom.

881
01:07:46,340 --> 01:07:49,560
<i>The only thing that's guaranteed in my life</i>

882
01:07:52,620 --> 01:07:57,300
<i>is the fact that you're my mom.</i>

883
01:07:58,300 --> 01:08:01,090
<i>And I'm so glad...</i>

884
01:08:05,570 --> 01:08:08,430
<i>and that I'm so happy.</i>

885
01:08:14,030 --> 01:08:16,400
<i>I really wanted to tell you that.</i>

886
01:08:18,950 --> 01:08:24,170
<i>Starting now, my everyday life</i>

887
01:08:24,170 --> 01:08:27,750
<i>will be a lot different than it is now.</i>

888
01:08:27,750 --> 01:08:30,230
<i>But it's okay.</i>

889
01:08:30,300 --> 01:08:34,100
<i>Because I know that hardships...</i>

890
01:08:35,460 --> 01:08:36,900
<i>can become-</i>

891
01:08:38,380 --> 01:08:41,750
<i>can become the beginning of happiness. I know that.</i>

892
01:08:41,750 --> 01:08:43,650
<i>So, I'm okay.</i>

893
01:08:44,730 --> 01:08:49,300
<i>And I have you by my side.</i>

894
01:08:50,490 --> 01:08:52,260
<i>So, I won't get scared.</i>

895
01:08:55,270 --> 01:08:56,870
<i>Mom...</i>

896
01:09:02,350 --> 01:09:04,590
Thank you so much...

897
01:09:08,040 --> 01:09:10,280
for being my mom.

898
01:09:13,230 --> 01:09:14,930
Really...

899
01:09:18,330 --> 01:09:20,680
<i>Thank you so much, Mom.</i>

900
01:09:57,440 --> 01:10:01,090
[Episode 11]

901
01:10:36,260 --> 01:10:40,280
<i> I'll be by your side </i>

902
01:10:40,300 --> 01:10:43,400
<i> I'll always be by your side </i>

903
01:10:43,460 --> 01:10:48,410
<i>I won't waste my body away for the sake
of people I love. I'll cherish it.</i>

904
01:10:48,410 --> 01:10:50,320
<i>I want to study.</i>

905
01:10:51,010 --> 01:10:53,200
<i>I think I'll be lonely.</i>

906
01:10:53,200 --> 01:10:56,450
<i>The things I overlooked as a doctor.</i>

907
01:10:57,700 --> 01:11:01,400
<i>Why do things like this only happen
to me? It feels unfair.</i>

908
01:11:01,400 --> 01:11:04,440
<i>I don't worry. You'll figure things out yourself.</i>

909
01:11:04,440 --> 01:11:06,480
<i>I'll return to Seoul now.</i>

910
01:11:06,480 --> 01:11:10,120
<i>Don't go. Why are you leaving?</i>

911
01:11:11,580 --> 01:11:14,680
<i>Let's meet again.</i>

912
01:11:14,680 --> 01:11:16,510
<i>I trust you, Hyo Ri.</i>

913
01:11:16,510 --> 01:11:23,220
<i>My radiant first love.</i>

914
01:11:23,220 --> 01:11:30,790
<i> The word that reminded me of
my forgotten dream made me fall in love </i>
